txt.en: 'Hullo, Maldo. Our stores of vegetables are stating to look a bit worn. Is there a chance we can buy some of your crop?'
'Without a doubt, master dwarf! Since trading for these fine tools, my work has take half as long!'
'Well and good! I'll have the usual payment delivered when the goods are collected.'
'But...but the hobbits have been very good about supplying me with delicious beer!'
'I will join, I will join! But you must stop slapping me....'
'Herluf! Someone brought you some nice, pretty, fragrant flowers!'
'What on earth am I supposed to do with flowers? How absurd.'
'Shocking reply! How could you not like flowers?'
'I just don't see what a dwarf could possibly do with...flowers.'
'Hmm, these are looking a bit tired. Perhaps I should have them replaced.'
